# shadcn/ui Usage Guidelines

This project uses **shadcn/ui** for all UI elements and components.

## Current Status

**Last Verified: 2026-01-21**

All components in `components/ui/` have been verified and are official shadcn/ui components:

- ✅ `button.tsx` - Official shadcn/ui Button component (with React.forwardRef)
- ✅ `card.tsx` - Official shadcn/ui Card component (with React.forwardRef, includes CardAction)
- ✅ `input.tsx` - Official shadcn/ui Input component (with React.forwardRef)
- ✅ `textarea.tsx` - Official shadcn/ui Textarea component (with React.forwardRef)
- ✅ `dropdown-menu.tsx` - Official shadcn/ui Dropdown Menu component (uses Radix UI primitives)
- ✅ `progress.tsx` - Official shadcn/ui Progress component (uses Radix UI primitives)
- ✅ `separator.tsx` - Official shadcn/ui Separator component (uses Radix UI primitives)

**No custom UI components exist in this project.**

## Configuration

shadcn/ui is configured in [components.json](mdc:components.json) with the following settings:
- Style: New York
- Base Color: Neutral
- Icon Library: lucide-react
- Components Path: `@/components/ui`
- Utils Path: `@/lib/utils`

## Adding Components

To add new shadcn/ui components to the project, use:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>
```

Examples:
```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
npx shadcn@latest add card
npx shadcn@latest add input
```

## Initialization (if needed)

If shadcn/ui is not initialized in the project, use:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init -d
```

## STRICT USAGE POLICY

**CRITICAL RULE: EXCLUSIVELY USE shadcn/ui COMPONENTS**

This project **EXCLUSIVELY** uses shadcn/ui components for ALL UI elements.

### Exception: Custom Components

**Custom UI components are ONLY allowed when:**
1. The component **does not exist** in the shadcn/ui library
2. You have verified on [shadcn/ui documentation](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components) that no equivalent exists
3. The component cannot be created by composing existing shadcn/ui components
4. The custom component is documented (see requirements below)

### Component Verification Requirement

**MANDATORY**: Before using any component from `components/ui/`, you must verify it is an **official shadcn/ui component**:

1. **Check the source**: Visit [shadcn/ui components](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components) to see the official implementation
2. **Compare the code**: Ensure the component matches the official shadcn/ui implementation
3. **Replace if custom**: If the component is custom, delete it and install the official version using `npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>`

### Official shadcn/ui Component Characteristics

Genuine shadcn/ui components typically have:
- Use of `React.forwardRef` for ref forwarding
- Consistent naming conventions and structure from shadcn/ui documentation
- Standard shadcn/ui className patterns
- TypeScript interfaces matching shadcn/ui specifications

### DO ✅

- **ALWAYS** use shadcn/ui components for every UI element
- **ALWAYS** check if a shadcn/ui component exists before writing any UI code
- **ALWAYS** verify that existing components in `components/ui/` are official shadcn/ui components
- **ALWAYS** replace custom components with official shadcn/ui versions
- **ALWAYS** add missing shadcn/ui components using `npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>`
- **ALWAYS** use the `cn()` utility from [lib/utils.ts](mdc:lib/utils.ts) for conditional class merging
- **ALWAYS** use lucide-react icons for all iconography needs
- **ALWAYS** leverage Tailwind CSS for styling customizations of shadcn/ui components

### DON'T ❌

- **NEVER** create custom UI components when shadcn/ui provides an equivalent
- **NEVER** write custom implementations when shadcn/ui provides the component
- **NEVER** assume a component in `components/ui/` is from shadcn/ui without verification
- **NEVER** write custom styled divs when a shadcn/ui component exists
- **NEVER** build forms without using shadcn/ui form components
- **NEVER** create custom dialogs, modals, or overlays - use shadcn/ui Dialog, Sheet, or Popover
- **NEVER** bypass shadcn/ui by creating "simple" custom components to save time
- **NEVER** modify the core structure of shadcn/ui components (only customize via className)
- **NEVER** create a custom component without exhaustive verification that shadcn/ui doesn't offer it

## Clerk Integration Requirements

### Authentication UI Components

When integrating Clerk authentication, you **MUST** follow these rules:

1. **Sign In/Sign Up Buttons**: Use shadcn/ui Button components
   ```typescript
   import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
   
   // ✅ CORRECT
   <Button onClick={() => openSignInModal()}>Sign In</Button>
   <Button onClick={() => openSignUpModal()}>Sign Up</Button>
   ```

2. **Authentication Modals**: Use shadcn/ui Dialog component for sign-in and sign-up
   ```typescript
   import { Dialog, DialogContent, DialogTrigger } from "@/components/ui/dialog";
   import { SignIn, SignUp } from "@clerk/nextjs";
   
   // ✅ CORRECT: Clerk forms in shadcn/ui Dialog
   <Dialog>
     <DialogTrigger asChild>
       <Button>Sign In</Button>
     </DialogTrigger>
     <DialogContent>
       <SignIn />
     </DialogContent>
   </Dialog>
   ```

3. **DO NOT** use Clerk's default UI components standalone:
   ```typescript
   // ❌ WRONG: Clerk components without shadcn/ui wrapper
   <SignInButton mode="modal" />
   
   // ✅ CORRECT: shadcn/ui Button with Clerk Dialog
   <Dialog>
     <DialogTrigger asChild>
       <Button>Sign In</Button>
     </DialogTrigger>
     <DialogContent>
       <SignIn />
     </DialogContent>
   </Dialog>
   ```

4. **User Profile/Settings**: Wrap in shadcn/ui Dialog or Sheet
   ```typescript
   // ✅ CORRECT
   <Sheet>
     <SheetTrigger asChild>
       <Button>Profile</Button>
     </SheetTrigger>
     <SheetContent>
       <UserProfile />
     </SheetContent>
   </Sheet>
   ```

