## Summary: When to Use Custom vs shadcn/ui Components

### ✅ Use shadcn/ui (99% of cases)

- Any standard UI component (buttons, inputs, cards, dialogs, etc.)
- Form elements and controls
- Navigation components
- Data display components
- Feedback components (alerts, toasts)
- Layout components

### ✅ Custom Components Allowed (Rare exceptions only)

**Only when ALL of these are true:**
1. Component does NOT exist in shadcn/ui
2. Cannot be created by composing shadcn/ui components
3. Specific functionality is required that shadcn/ui doesn't provide
4. Verified in shadcn/ui documentation (with date)
5. Properly documented with JSDoc
6. Placed in `components/custom/` or appropriate directory (NOT `components/ui/`)
7. Built using shadcn/ui components as building blocks when possible

**Examples of acceptable custom components:**
- `Timeline` - Not provided by shadcn/ui
- `KanbanBoard` - Complex drag-and-drop specific to app needs
- `ChartWidget` - Integration with specific charting library
- `CodeEditor` - Integration with Monaco or similar

**Examples of UNACCEPTABLE custom components:**
- ❌ Custom `Button` - Use shadcn/ui Button
- ❌ Custom `Modal` - Use shadcn/ui Dialog
- ❌ Custom `Card` - Use shadcn/ui Card
- ❌ Custom form inputs - Use shadcn/ui Input, Textarea, Select
- ❌ Custom `Dropdown` - Use shadcn/ui DropdownMenu

